    "body": "@zcbenz I've tried this, but I **still** get the white screen?\n\nIn main.js\n\n```\nmainWindow = new BrowserWindow({\n      'width': size.width,\n      'height': size.height,\n      'frame': false,\n      'transparent': true,\n      'show': false,\n      'resizable': false,\n      'auto-hide-menu-bar': true\n    });\n```\n\nand then in my index.html\n\n```\ndocument.addEventListener(\"DOMContentLoaded\", function(event) { \n    showWindow();\n});\n\nfunction showWindow()\n{\n    remote.getCurrentWindow().setFullScreen(true);\n}\n```\n\nWhile I'm waiting for the showWindow function to fire the whole screen is white!\n\n**UPDATE: Even if I do:**\n\n```\nfunction showWindow()\n{\n    setTimeout(function(){\n        remote.getCurrentWindow().setFullScreen(true);\n    }, 5000);\n}\n```\n\nThe screen goes white for a second and then fades in my window content. So it's nothing to do with the document ready, but rather the initial showing of window content!\n\nTesting on OS X Yosemite\n"
